<document "User's Guide" "users-guide">

<blockquote>
This "User's Guide" is nothing but a reformatted "Progeny User's Guide".
Contents are adjusted for the standard Debian system.

<p>Over 300 pages with good tutorial to start using the Debian system
from GUI desktop and shell command line.

<doctable>
  <authors "Progeny Linux Systems, Inc.">
  <maintainer "Osamu Aoki (&#38738;&#26408; &#20462;)">
  <status>
  Useful itself as a tutorial.  It is expected to provide
  a nice starting point for the post-woody install manual.
  </status>
  <availability>
# langs="en" isn't redundant, it adds the needed language suffix to the link
  <inddpcvs name="users-guide" index="users-guide" langs="en" formats="html txt pdf">
